description:
As cheaper heroin floods the East coast of America, a generation of young people already hooked on prescription opiates has found the drug to be a more affordable substitute. Robert Moore reports on the brutal reality of life as an addict, and the impossible task faced by campaigners and law enforcement to get this epidemic under control as it spreads into the suburbs. Also in this episode, Geraint Vincent reports from the West Bank and John Irvine spends a day in the Burj Khalifa - the world's tallest building.
